review_text: Such a wonderful assembling area. The first time feels like in one of the European cities. Just needed a public restroom.

(Translated by Google) Nice place with colorful furniture. Beautiful place of life. Too bad it isn't greener. I really like the illuminated pendant light which provides a lot of warmth in winter.

(Original)
Belle place avec du mobilier coloré. Beau lieu de vie. Dommage qu’elle ne soit pas plus verte. J’aime beaucoup la suspension illumine qui apporte beaucoup de chaleur en hiver.

(Translated by Google) I love this little park. It just lacks greenery and would be perfect. :)

(Original)
J’adore ce petit parc. Il manque simplement de la verdure et il serait parfait. :)

(Translated by Google) Nice place to chat with friends

(Original)
Belle place pour jaser avec les amis

(Translated by Google) My Plateau guide told me that this park is a tribute to Jean-Pierre Ferland. Ok his musicography is not from my time, but I often go to his hometown. Apparently, this park is a place where the atmosphere is there for a lot, in summer! And I allowed myself to Googling the expression "flower-of-macadame" ... prostitute who solicits !!!!

(Original)
Ma guide du Plateau ma dit que ce parc est un hommage à Jean-Pierre Ferland. Ok sa musicographie n'est pas de mon époque, mais je vais souvent dans sa ville de résidence. Apparament, ce parc est un lieu où l'ambiance y est pour beaucoup, en été! Et je me suis permis de Googler l'expression "fleur-de-macadame"... prostituée qui racole!!!!

(Translated by Google) Always better than the gas station lying there

(Original)
